---
import MainLayout from "../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
import CalculatorCard from "../components/CalculatorCard.astro";
---

<MainLayout
  title="Free Betting Calculators and Betting Maths Guides"
  description="Free betting calculators and plain-English guides to help you understand odds, overround, dutching, hedging, accumulators, bookmaker margin and betting jargon."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">Betting calculators and plain-English guides</p>
    <h1>Understand the odds. Use the maths. Bet smarter.</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      Betting Maths helps you understand odds, stakes, overround, dutching, hedging, accumulators, back and lay betting, bookmaker margin and common betting jargon with simple calculators and practical examples.
    </p>
    <div class="button-row">
      <a class="button primary" href="/calculators/overround-calculator/">Start with the Overround Calculator</a>
      <a class="button secondary" href="/glossary/betting-jargon-explained/">Explore the Betting Glossary</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="content-card intro-panel">
    <h2>What is Betting Maths?</h2>
    <p>
      Betting Maths is a free betting education and calculator site. It is designed to explain how odds, implied probability, overround, dutching, hedging, accumulators and bookmaker margins work in plain English.
    </p>
    <p>
      The aim is not to provide betting tips or guaranteed profit systems. The aim is to help you understand the numbers behind betting markets so you can read odds, calculate outcomes and understand risk more clearly.
    </p>
  </section>

  <h2>Popular betting calculators</h2>
  <div class="grid">
    <CalculatorCard
      title="Overround Calculator"
      description="Work out the total book percentage and bookmaker margin built into a betting market."
      href="/calculators/overround-calculator/"
    />
    <CalculatorCard
      title="Odds Converter"
      description="Convert decimal, fractional and American odds, and calculate implied probability."
      href="/calculators/odds-converter/"
    />
    <CalculatorCard
      title="Dutching Calculator"
      description="Split a total stake across two or more selections for a balanced return."
      href="/calculators/dutching-calculator/"
    />
    <CalculatorCard
      title="Hedge Bet Calculator"
      description="Calculate back and lay hedge stakes, lay liability, commission and possible profit or loss."
      href="/calculators/hedge-bet-calculator/"
    />
    <CalculatorCard
      title="Accumulator Calculator"
      description="Multiply odds across multiple selections and calculate acca returns, profit and implied probability."
      href="/calculators/accumulator-calculator/"
    />
  </div>

  <section class="content-card article-section">
    <h2>Learn the key betting maths concepts</h2>
    <p>
      Start with these guides if you want to understand how betting markets are priced, why the odds are usually built in the bookmaker’s favour, and why betting systems should be treated carefully.
    </p>

    <div class="guide-grid">
      <a class="guide-card" href="/guides/what-is-overround/">
        <span>Guide</span>
        <h3>What Is Overround in Betting?</h3>
        <p>Learn how book percentage and bookmaker margin are calculated.</p>
      </a>

      <a class="guide-card" href="/guides/how-to-hedge-a-bet/">
        <span>Guide</span>
        <h3>How to Hedge a Bet</h3>
        <p>Understand back and lay hedging, lay liability, commission and greening up.</p>
      </a>

      <a class="guide-card" href="/guides/what-is-dutching/">
        <span>Guide</span>
        <h3>What Is Dutching in Betting?</h3>
        <p>Learn how dutching splits stakes across multiple selections.</p>
      </a>

      <a class="guide-card" href="/guides/how-bookmakers-make-money/">
        <span>Guide</span>
        <h3>How Bookmakers Make Money</h3>
        <p>Understand overround, odds movement, weight of money and liability management.</p>
      </a>

      <a class="guide-card" href="/guides/can-you-always-beat-the-bookie/">
        <span>Guide</span>
        <h3>Can You Always Beat the Bookie?</h3>
        <p>Learn why guaranteed betting systems are risky and what maths can actually show.</p>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="content-card article-section">
    <h2>Betting jargon explained</h2>
    <p>
      Betting can be full of confusing terms: acca, overround, lay bet, liability, vig, juice, dutching, hedging, value betting, underround and more.
    </p>
    <p>
      Our betting glossary explains common betting terms in plain English and links important maths terms to the right calculator.
    </p>

    <div class="button-row">
      <a class="button primary" href="/glossary/betting-jargon-explained/">Open the Betting Jargon Glossary</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="content-card article-section">
    <h2>Start with a simple example</h2>
    <p>
      A football match might have odds of 2.10 for the home win, 3.40 for the draw and 3.60 for the away win. Converted into implied probability, those prices add up to 104.81%.
    </p>

    <table class="example-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Outcome</th>
          <th>Decimal odds</th>
          <th>Implied probability</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>Home win</td>
          <td>2.10</td>
          <td>47.62%</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Draw</td>
          <td>3.40</td>
          <td>29.41%</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Away win</td>
          <td>3.60</td>
          <td>27.78%</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <p>
      That means the market has a 4.81% overround. This is one simple example of how betting maths helps explain bookmaker margin.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="content-card article-section">
    <h2>Accumulator example</h2>
    <p>
      Accumulators multiply odds together. For example, decimal odds of 2.00, 1.80 and 2.50 combine to make accumulator odds of 9.00.
    </p>

    <table class="example-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Selection</th>
          <th>Decimal odds</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>Selection 1</td>
          <td>2.00</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Selection 2</td>
          <td>1.80</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Selection 3</td>
          <td>2.50</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <p>
      A £10 stake at combined odds of 9.00 would return £90, including £80 profit. The <a href="/calculators/accumulator-calculator/">Accumulator Calculator</a> works this out automatically and also shows the implied probability.
    </p>
  </section>

  <div class="callout">
    <strong>Responsible note:</strong> Betting Maths is an educational calculator site. It does not provide betting tips, financial advice or guaranteed profit strategies. Betting always involves risk.
  </div>

  <style>
    .intro-panel {
      margin-top: 1.25rem;
    }

    .article-section {
      margin-top: 1.25rem;
    }

    .guide-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
      gap: 1rem;
      margin-top: 1rem;
    }

    .guide-card {
      display: block;
      padding: 1.15rem;
      border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
      border-radius: 14px;
      background: var(--color-bg);
    }

    .guide-card:hover {
      border-color: rgba(31, 138, 91, 0.45);
      transform: translateY(-2px);
    }

    .guide-card span {
      display: inline-flex;
      margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
      padding: 0.15rem 0.55rem;
      border-radius: 999px;
      background: #eef8f3;
      color: var(--color-green-dark);
      font-size: 0.78rem;
      font-weight: 800;
    }

    .guide-card h3 {
      margin-bottom: 0.35rem;
    }

    .guide-card p {
      margin: 0;
      color: var(--color-muted);
    }

    .example-table {
      width: 100%;
      border-collapse: collapse;
      background: white;
      border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
      border-radius: 14px;
      overflow: hidden;
      margin: 1rem 0;
    }

    .example-table th,
    .example-table td {
      padding: 0.75rem;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
      text-align: left;
      vertical-align: middle;
    }

    .example-table th {
      color: var(--color-navy);
      background: #f4f7fa;
      font-size: 0.9rem;
    }

    .example-table tr:last-child td {
      border-bottom: 0;
    }

    .article-section a {
      color: var(--color-green-dark);
      font-weight: 800;
      text-decoration: underline;
      text-underline-offset: 3px;
    }

    @media (max-width: 760px) {
      .guide-grid {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      }
    }
  </style>
</MainLayout>
